- `get-canvas-kit-upgrade-guides`: Version upgrade information

**Available resources (use FetchMcpResource):**
- `docs://tokens/color-palette` - Color system and palettes
- `docs://tokens/color-tokens` - Token naming and usage
- `docs://tokens/color-roles` - Semantic color roles
- `docs://tokens/color-contrast` - Accessibility contrast guidelines
- `docs://upgrade-guides/11.0-UPGRADE-GUIDE` - Canvas Kit v11 guide

**How to use:**
1. Call `CallMcpTool` with server `user-canvas-kit-mcp` and tool name
2. Use `FetchMcpResource` to read specific documentation

**Common Canvas Kit Components (v11):**
- Layout: `Box`, `Flex`, `Card`
- Buttons: `PrimaryButton`, `SecondaryButton`, `TertiaryButton`, `ToolbarIconButton`
- Inputs: `TextInput`, `Select`, `Radio`, `Checkbox`
- Display: `Table` (with `.Head`, `.Body`, `.Row`, `.Header`, `.Cell`)
- Navigation: `Tabs` (with `.List`, `.Item`, `.Panel` - requires `data-id` props), `Menu`
- Text: `Heading`, `BodyText`, `Text`
- Icons: `SystemIcon`, `Avatar`
- Popups: `Modal`, `Popup`, `Toast`

**Design Tokens (from Canvas Kit v11):**
- `colors` - Color palette (blueberry, cinnamon, soap, blackPepper, greenApple, cantaloupe, etc.)
- `space` - Spacing scale (xxxs, xxs, xs, s, m, l, xl, xxl, xxxl)
- `type` - Typography scale

**CRITICAL Canvas Kit v11 Requirements:**
⚠️ **Canvas Kit v11 REQUIRES `@workday/canvas-tokens-web` to be installed**
- Components use CSS variables that are ONLY defined by Canvas Tokens Web
- Without this package, components will have NO STYLING (no colors, spacing, borders, etc.)
- Must import token CSS files in the app entry point (main.tsx/index.tsx):
  ```tsx
  import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/base/_variables.css';
  import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/system/_variables.css';
  import '@workday/canvas-tokens-web/css/brand/_variables.css';
  ```

**Component-Specific Requirements:**

**Tabs Component:**
- Requires `initialTab` prop to set which tab loads by default
- Use `data-id` prop (NOT `name` or `id`) on both `Tabs.Item` and `Tabs.Panel` to link them
- Example:
  ```tsx
  <Tabs initialTab="overview">
    <Tabs.List>
      <Tabs.Item data-id="overview">Overview</Tabs.Item>
    </Tabs.List>
    <Tabs.Panel data-id="overview">Content</Tabs.Panel>
  </Tabs>
  ```

**Table Component:**
- Must use compound component pattern with `.Head`, `.Body`, `.Row`, `.Header`, `.Cell`
- NOT the old `<thead>`, `<tbody>` pattern
- Example:
  ```tsx
  <Table>
    <Table.Head>
      <Table.Row>
        <Table.Header>Name</Table.Header>
      </Table.Row>
    </Table.Head>
    <Table.Body>
      <Table.Row>
        <Table.Cell>Value</Table.Cell>
      </Table.Row>
    </Table.Body>
  </Table>
  ```

**TextInput Component:**
- Style props go directly on the component, NOT via an `inputProps` object
- Use `style={{}}` prop for custom styling

**Standard Workday Top Navigation Pattern:**
- Left: Hamburger menu (`ToolbarIconButton` with `justifyIcon`) + Workday logo
- Center: Search bar (`TextInput` with search icon positioned absolutely)
- Right: User avatar
- White background with bottom border
- Use responsive flexbox layout

**DO NOT:**
- Reference canvas.workday.com or external design system docs
- Forget to install and import Canvas Tokens Web CSS files
- Use old pre-v11 component patterns (like `<thead>` in tables)
- Add custom animations or micro-interactions
- Over-engineer with complex styling patterns
- Use `name` or `id` for Tabs - must use `data-id`

**DO:**
- ALWAYS verify Canvas Tokens Web is installed and imported
- Use Canvas Kit components as-is with their built-in styling
- Use Canvas Kit's margin/padding props (marginBottom="m", padding="l")
- Use `data-id` for Tabs component linking
- Use compound components (Table, Tabs) correctly
- Keep implementations simple and straightforward
- Trust Canvas Kit's default behaviors
- Check Canvas Kit v11 upgrade guide for breaking changes

